parameters: Mage Relm: Nothing happens even if you touch it...

Mage Relm: This is clearly the power of magic... but I have
never seen or heard of anything like this before...!

Explorer Armada: This is the seal of approval from a mage
belonging to the Magic Academy! There's no doubt that
there's something incredible deep inside here.
Explorer Armada: So, do you understand anything, little one?

Mage Relm: Please stop, little one! It swallows voices... It
probably won't swallow your voice.

Mage Relm: The magic of voice might be the key! However, the
spellbook of the sound-devouring demon, Kowan, has been
lost.

Explorer Armada: ...I'll investigate various things.
Everyone, please search for the magic of voice.
Clea: Touching the dragon statue... wahh!!
Clea: Amazing... the voice is being sucked in...

Explorer Armada: This is what I discovered. How should the
mages from the academy analyze it?

Mage Relm: I believe that the voice is definitely the key.
Voice, the magic of voice, could it be the sound-devouring
demon Kowan...!
Mage Relm: Yes, let's ask Phoni-san for help!

Priestess Sophia: Oh my, I wonder if your promise with Olden
is going well?

Thief Nora: Um, c-can you keep this a secret...? Is that
okay?

Explorer Armada: Ahaha! I just want to go deeper into this
place, so I haven't heard anything.

Explorer Armada: I'm willing to risk my life for this
opportunity. I want your cooperation.

Clea: It would be helpful if you could say that. Let's go
meet Phoni-san.

Explorer Armada: I'm the explorer Armada, nice to meet you!
Please take care of me!

Voice Priestess Phoni: I am Phoni, pleased to meet you.
Please take care of me.
Voice Priestess Phoni: So, what should I do?

Clea: May I ask you to touch the dragon statue and try
shouting loudly?
Voice Priestess Phoni: Yes... I will give it a try.

Mage Relm: It seems like we're experiencing the same
phenomenon... Perhaps we need something else... Maybe the
pitch of our voices... or...

Priestess Sophia: Hmm, I wonder... How about we have a drink
first and then think about it?
Thief Nora: Um, may I ask something?

Thief Nora: Could it be that we just need to mimic the
dragon's voice as we see it...?

Voice Priestess Phoni: I will give it a try... First, I will
touch the stone statue...
Voice Priestess Phoni: Here I go!
Explorer Armada: The stone statue... it shattered...!

Explorer Armada: The door opened...! Look, it's amazing, it
really opened!

Explorer Armada: Thanks to everyone, we did it! Now, let's
go inside the door!

Explorer Armada: Now, take a look! This is my secret weapon
as an explorer!
Clea: A dragon statue...! What kind of place is this?

Explorer Armada: It was about 10 years ago... The crystals
in Valier were running out, and the residents were getting
anxious.

Explorer Armada: This is the place mentioned in the old
legends passed down in Valier, where they started digging
tunnels in the forbidden area... the mountain where demons
reside.

Explorer Armada: And then a major cave-in accident occurred,
and many people died. It was the day when the spirit of
Valier was completely broken.

Mage Relm: And what does this place have to do with
anything!?

Explorer Armada: Among those caught in the cave-in, there
was one survivor. That person obtained three things from
that accident.

Explorer Armada: The scar on my face, this room, and this
accessory.
Clea: Armada-san is the only survivor...

Explorer Armada: It seems like I was pushed into this space,
and that's where I found this accessory. Take a look!

Explorer Armada: It shines as beautifully as gold, doesn't
it? But strangely, I don't feel any weight at all.

Explorer Armada: I believe that the one who created this
space and the accessory was a completely different
civilization from ours.

Mage Relm: Is this the civilization of demons that was born
during the era of the three goddesses!?

Explorer Armada: That's right, little one! There should be a
civilization of demons beyond this door!

Explorer Armada: I want you to help me find a way to open
this place! I feel limited in my solo investigation, so
please, I'm begging you!
Please tell me what you found in the room
Please tell me about the era of the Three Goddesses
I want you to tell me about the civilization of demons
I don't have anything I want to ask
部屋で発見したことを教えて欲しい

Explorer Armada: There's a statue of a dragon, right? If you
touch it and shout loudly, something strange will happen.

Explorer Armada: It feels like your voice gets sucked in...
Maybe it's best to try it out for yourself.
三女神の時代について教えて欲しい

Explorer Armada: According to the founder of magic, Subma,
65 out of the 72 demons were sealed in grimoires.

Explorer Armada: In order to counter the remaining seven
pillars, the goddess Imiserinos granted humanity
immortality, eternal youth, clairvoyance, freedom from
illness, satiety, regeneration, and telepathy.

Explorer Armada: Afterwards, it seems that a hero appeared
and defeated the seven demons, but it seems that the
excessive power granted was taken away again.
悪魔の文明について教えて欲しい

Explorer Armada: Among those who no longer feared demons due
to the goddess Imiserinos, there were also those who tried
to prosper by cooperating with the demons.

Explorer Armada: It seems that the civilization of demons
that was created at that time had technology and knowledge
that far surpassed what we have now.

Explorer Armada: In the end, it is said that the entire
civilization of demons was destroyed along with the anger of
the goddesses.

Explorer Armada: But that ruins actually still exist... I've
been continuing my investigations and research with that
belief.
Mage Relm: It seems to be sealed with powerful magic...
